Pre-Game Insights: The Braves have been in a pseudo-do-or-die mode for a while now, but on Wednesday night, they will face their second elimination game in three contests.
The Braves have Max Fried starting tonight on regular rest.
The Padres have Joe Musgrove starting.
Fried is coming off a game where he nearly Madduxed the Royals, finishing with a 9/2 K/BB ratio in 8 2⁄3 innings.
Musgrove missed a huge part of this season with elbow inflammation, but nonetheless posted 1.4 fWAR in 19 starts spanning 99 2⁄3 innings.
